#include <iostream>
#include <cstdlib>
#include <cstdio>
#include <string>

inline bool isLeap(int y) {
	if(y % 400 == 0)
		return true;
	else if(y%4 == 0 && y%100 != 0)
		return true;
	return false;
}

int main() {
	int t, count;
	std::string date, d, m, y;
	int days;
	scanf("%d", &t);
	for(count=1; count <=t; count++) {
		std::cin>>date;
		d = date.substr(0, 2);
		m = date.substr(3, 3);
		y = date.substr(7);
		
		if(m == "JAN")
			days = 0;
		else if(m == "FEB")
			days = 31;
		else if(m == "MAR")
			days = 59;
		else if(m == "APR")
			days = 90;
		else if(m == "MAY")
			days = 120;
		else if(m == "JUN")
			days = 151;
		else if(m == "JUL")
			days = 181;
		else if(m == "AUG")
			days = 212;
		else if(m == "SEP")
			days = 243;
		else if(m == "OCT")
			days = 273;
		else if(m == "NOV")
			days = 304;
		else if(m == "DEC")
			days = 334;
		if(isLeap(std::stoi(y)) && m != "JAN" && m != "FEB")
			days++;
		
		days += stoi(d);

		if(days <= 300)
			printf("Case %d: %d Hundreds\n", count, days);
		else if(days <= 360)
			printf("Case %d: %d Tens\n", count, days-300);
		else
			printf("Case %d: %d Ones\n", count, days-360);
		
	}
	return 0;
}
